# ovh_vps_service_info

Manages service-level settings (such as renewal configuration) for an OVHcloud VPS.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/vps_service_info/example_1.tf"}}

## Argument Reference

The following arguments are supported:

* `service_name` - (Required) The service_name of your VPS.
* `renew` - (Optional) Renewal configuration for the service.
  * `automatic` - (Optional) Whether automatic renewal is enabled.
  * `delete_at_expiration` - (Optional) Whether to delete the service at expiration.
  * `forced` - (Optional) Whether renewal is forced.
  * `period` - (Optional) Renewal period.

## Attributes Reference

(See generated docs/resources/vps_service_info.md for the full attribute list.)

The following attributes are exported:

* `id` - The ID of the service.
* `status` - Current status of the service.
* `expiration` - Expiration date of the service.
